observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management:

require the MENRO in coordination with the support Offices to operationalize the MRF;  


strategically plan, manage, and execute program/projects with a view to ensuring efficiency, economy and effectiveness in the operations of government resources;

require the MENRO in coordination with the Municipal Management Board to respond to the matter and materialize the safe closure and rehabilitation of the dumpsite and provide 10-year Solid Waste Management Plan/Program for the safe and sanitary management of the solid waste generation consistent with the national framework and in accordance with the Act and of the policies set by the National Solid Waste Management Commission; and

require the Municipal Management Board to strategically plan to ensure implementation and enforcement of the provisions of the Act.

We recommended the following:

The Municipal Treasurer exerts more effort to collect the receivables by sending collection letters to the named creditors specially those still living and with capacity to pay;

Enforcement of the conditions of loan repayment as well as the penalty provision in case of default in payment; 

With the help of the MSWO, MAO and other Department concerns, conduct a thorough verification and validation of creditors who are already deceased and incapacitated to pay; and

Request for write-off of accounts receivables from concerned government agency in order to reflect the actual/correct loan receivables of the Municipality.

We recommended that Management:
require the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Engineer to trace the status and history of these constructions in progress accounts;
direct the Municipal Accountant to transfer completed projects to appropriate PPE accounts and make the necessary adjustments relative to the current and prior years unrecorded depreciation expense of any finished CIP-agency asset.

We recommended that Management:

(a)	require the MENRO in coordination with the support Offices to operationalize the MRF;  

(b)	strategically plan, manage, and execute program/projects with a view to ensuring efficiency, economy and effectiveness in the operations of government resources;

(c)	require the MENRO in coordination with the Municipal Management Board to respond to the matter and materialize the safe closure and rehabilitation of the dumpsite and provide 10-year Solid Waste Management Plan/Program for the safe and sanitary management of the solid waste generation consistent with the national framework and in accordance with the Act and of the policies set by the National Solid Waste Management Commission; and

(d)	require the Municipal Management Board to strategically plan to ensure implementation and enforcement of the provisions of the Act.

We recommended the Management to:

(a)	direct the Inventory Committee to diligently conduct the physical inventory taking of supplies and materials once every semester and prepare and submit the corresponding RPCI to the Audit Team within the set timeline;

(b)	require the MSW Officer and DRRM Officer to submit the required documentations to record liquidation of Inventory Accounts;

(c)	direct the Municipal Accountant to prepare the necessary adjusting entries upon receipt of liquidation reports to reflect the true and correct balances; and

(d)	maintain Stock Cards and Subsidiary Ledgers of each Inventory Accounts.

We recommended the following:

a.	The Municipal Treasurer exerts more effort to collect the receivables by sending collection letters to the named creditors specially those still living and with capacity to pay;

b.	Enforcement of the conditions of loan repayment as well as the penalty provision in case of default in payment; 

c.	With the help of the MSWO, MAO and other Department concerns, conduct a thorough verification and validation of creditors who are already deceased and incapacitated to pay; and

d.	Request for write-off of accounts receivables from concerned government agency in order to reflect the actual/correct loan receivables of the Municipality.

